arguments.prompt:
You are building a Blazor Web App for a veterinary clinic. The project is already scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-672a16a039934058a46e543b6efe6363/VetClinic` with:
- Interactive Server mode (global) with Individual auth
- .NET 11 preview, SQLite database
- EF Core Identity already configured

Your job is to implement the full application. Here's what needs to be done:

## 1. Data Models (create `/tmp/sv-672a16a039934058a46e543b6efe6363/VetClinic/Data/Models.cs`)

Create these entity classes in namespace `VetClinic.Data`:

```csharp
public class Patient
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; } = string.Empty; // Pet name
    public string Species { get; set; } = string.Empty; // Dog, Cat, etc.
    public string Breed { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime DateOfBirth { get; set; }
    public string OwnerName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string OwnerPhone { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string OwnerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime RegisteredAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public List<MedicalRecord> MedicalRecords { get; set; } = new();
    public List<Appointment> Appointments { get; set; } = new();
    public List<Invoice> Invoices { get; set; } = new();
}

public class MedicalRecord
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PatientId { get; set; }
    public Patient Patient { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime Date { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public string Diagnosis { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Treatment { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Notes { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string VetName { get; set; } = string.Empty; // staff who wrote it
}

public class Appointment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PatientId { get; set; }
    public Patient Patient { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime StartTime { get; set; }
    public DateTime EndTime { get; set; }
    public string Reason { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public AppointmentStatus Status { get; set; } = AppointmentStatus.Scheduled;
    public string VetName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Notes { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}

public enum AppointmentStatus
{
    Scheduled,
    Completed,
    Cancelled
}

public class Invoice
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PatientId { get; set; }
    public Patient Patient { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime IssuedAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public decimal Amount { get; set; }
    public bool IsPaid { get; set; }
    public DateTime? PaidAt { get; set; }
    public string PaymentMethod { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

## 2. Update ApplicationDbContext (`/tmp/sv-672a16a039934058a46e543b6efe6363/VetClinic/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs`)

Add DbSets for Patient, MedicalRecord, Appointment, Invoice. Add OnModelCreating for decimal precision on Invoice.Amount.

## 3. Create Services (`/tmp/sv-672a16a039934058a46e543b6efe6363/VetClinic/Services/`)

Create a `Services` directory with:

**PatientService.cs** - CRUD for patients, search by name/owner, get with medical records
**AppointmentService.cs** - CRUD for appointments, get by date range, check availability (no overlapping appointments for same vet in 30-min slots)
**BillingService.cs** - Create invoice, process payment, get payment history

Each service should be registered as Scoped in DI. Use EF Core directly (no repository pattern needed).

## 4. Update Program.cs

Register the three services after the existing DI registrations. Also add this before `app.Run()`:
```csharp
using (var scope = app.Services.CreateScope())
{
    var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<ApplicationDbContext>();
    db.Database.Migrate();
}
```

Also change `options.SignIn.RequireConfirmedAccount = true` to `false` so staff can log in immediately after registration without email confirmation.

## 5. Create Pages

Delete: `Counter.razor`, `Weather.razor`, `Auth.razor` from `Components/Pages/`

Create these pages in `Components/Pages/`:

### Home.razor - Replace existing
Dashboard showing today's appointments count, total patients, pending invoices. Quick links to each section.
Use `@attribute [Authorize]` on every page.

### Patients/Index.razor (`@page "/patients"`)
- Search box (filters as you type)
- Table of patients (Name, Species, Breed, Owner, Phone)
- "Register New" button opens inline form
- Click patient name navigates to detail

### Patients/Detail.razor (`@page "/patients/{Id:int}"`)
- Patient info (editable fields with Save button)
- Medical History section: list of records with Add New form
- Add Treatment Note: diagnosis, treatment, notes fields

### Appointments/Index.razor (`@page "/appointments"`)
- Date picker to select day (defaults to today)
- Time grid showing 30-min slots from 8:00 to 18:00
- Each slot shows if booked (patient name + vet) or available
- Click available slot to open create form (select patient, vet, reason)
- Click booked slot to see details with Reschedule/Cancel buttons
- Reschedule shows a date+time picker

### Billing/Index.razor (`@page "/billing"`)
- "Create Invoice" form: select patient, description, amount
- Table of invoices (recent first): Patient, Description, Amount, Status, Date
- Unpaid invoices have a "Process Payment" button that opens payment method selector
- Filter toggle: All / Unpaid / Paid

## 6. Update NavMenu.razor

Replace the Counter/Weather/Auth links with:
- Home (href="")
- Patients (href="patients") 
- Appointments (href="appointments")
- Billing (href="billing")

Keep the AuthorizeView section for login/logout/account management.

## 7. Create AGENTS.md at project root

Content:
```
# VetClinic

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| **Interactivity Mode** | Server |
| **Interactivity Scope** | Global |

## Rendering configuration
This project uses global Interactive Server with prerendering.
Created with `dotnet new blazor -int Server -ai -au Individual`.

All pages are interactive by default via `<Routes @rendermode="InteractiveServer" />` in `App.razor`.

## Adding new components
- Create new `.razor` files in `Components/Pages/` for routable pages or `Components/` for shared components.
- All pages are already interactive. No need to add `@rendermode` to individual components.

## Data access
- Components can inject services directly — EF Core DbContext, file system, server-only APIs. No HTTP API layer needed.

## Authentication
- ASP.NET Core Identity is configured with Individual accounts.
- Identity pages under `Components/Account/` are always static SSR — do not add `@rendermode` to them.
- All application pages require authentication via `@attribute [Authorize]`.

## Don'ts
- Don't add `@rendermode InteractiveServer` to pages — global interactivity is already configured in `App.razor`.
- Don't add `@rendermode` to Identity/Account pages — they must stay static SSR.
- Don't inject `HttpContext` in interactive components — it's not available during SignalR circuit lifetime.
- Don't use browser APIs (localStorage, DOM) directly — use `IJSRuntime` interop instead.
```

## 8. Create EF Migration

Run: `cd /tmp/sv-672a16a039934058a46e543b6efe6363/VetClinic && dotnet ef migrations add AddVetClinicEntities`

## 9. Build and verify

Run: `cd /tmp/sv-672a16a039934058a46e543b6efe6363/VetClinic && dotnet build`

Fix any compilation errors.

## Implementation Notes:
- Use `@inject` for services in Razor pages
- Use `EditForm` with `Model` binding for forms
- Use `@bind` for two-way binding on inputs
- For the appointment calendar, render a simple table/grid with time slots
- For search, use `@oninput` with debounce or simple filtering
- All pages must have `@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization` and `@attribute [Authorize]`
- Put `@using VetClinic.Data` and `@using VetClinic.Services` in `_Imports.razor`

